📚 Arrays in JavaScript (Detailed)
Arrays are ordered collections used to store multiple values in a single variable.
e.g:
const fruits = ["Apple", "Banana", "Mango"];

🔧 Functions in JavaScript (Detailed)
Functions are reusable blocks of code that perform specific tasks.
function greet(name) {
  return "Hello, " + name;
}
console.log(greet("Ali")); // Output: Hello, Ali
🔄 Conditional Statements (Detailed)
Used to make decisions based on conditions.

✅ if...else
🟨 else if
🔁 switch Statement
